  The repository contains three related implementations of the distributional optimal transport (DOT) search strategy. 
1.DOT-Open-Policy: MATLAB implementation for continuous CEC2017 benchmark optimization.
2.DOT-NAS-Open-Policy: MATLAB DOT search adapted to NASBench-101 neural architecture search, with a persistent Python NASBench daemon.
3.DOT-WireMask-Open-Policy: Python implementation for ISPD2005 macro placement, with random search, Bayesian optimization, DOT search, and a MATLAB bridge.
  Repository Layout
.
|-- DOT-Open-Policy/
|   |-- OpTr_by_SinkHorn.m          # Main MATLAB CEC2017 experiment script
|   |-- DisOT_ProbMeasure.m         # DOT optimizer for continuous functions
|   |-- Sinkhorn_OTcomputing.m      # Entropic OT / Sinkhorn solver
|   |-- cec17_func.cpp              # CEC2017 source
|   `-- cec17_func.mexw64           # Windows MATLAB MEX binary
|
|-- DOT-NAS-Open-Policy/
|   |-- OpTr_by_SinkHorn.m          # Main MATLAB NASBench-101 experiment script
|   |-- DisOT_ProbMeasure.m         # DOT optimizer for 26D architecture encoding
